Dempsey said the U.S. has peer competitors in cyberwarfare and went as far as calling it a level playing field. That makes him very uncomfortable, Dempsey said.

He did not go into detail about steps the U.S. could take to beef up its cyber defences.

Dempsey's comments follow an attack on Sony pictures late last year by a North Korean hacking group calling themselves 'Guardians of Peace'.

The hackers released a series of embarrassing emails, including correspondence between Sony Pictures co-chairwoman Amy Pascal and producer Scott Rudin, who referred to Angelina Jolie as 'a minimally talented spoiled brat'.

