Parts of the script for the new James Bond film Spectre, which is due to be released in 2015, were also released by the hackers, as well as emails about the plot lines.

The Sony letters were published ahead of the release of 'The Interview', a film which takes the assassination of North Korean leader Kim Jong-Un as its subject matter. Several cinemas refused to show the film, which Sony first pulled but later made available on the internet.

